&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Senior Mental Health Practitioner&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Community Mental Health&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;£31,365 - £37,890 (Band 6) pro rata&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;18 hours per week&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;span&gt;The Community Mental Health Team are developing our physical health care provision. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are looking for a Senior Mental Health Practitioner to work primarily in our Nurse Led Clinics.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;You will be Registered Mental Health Nurse with an interest in working with adults who have eating disorders and the physical health of people who use the Mental Health Service. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Ideally you will be competent with taking bloods, ECGs and administering depot medication however, training and support to develop these skills can be provided. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are looking for a Nurse who can work 9-5 on Tuesdays and Thursdays with flexibility for the remaining hours.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;If you are interested in the above post and would like any more information or an informal discussion, please contact Karen Sims or Jo Cullum on 01983 525254.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
